             <h4>KEY FINDINGS</h4>
             <p>James <strong>enjoys cooking</strong>, he used to cook every da, sometimes even complex recipes, before he got married 9 months ago. Now <strong>he cooks 2/3 times a month</strong> because his wife is an amazing cook, she cooks very traditional Chinese food following her mum’s recipes. During the weekend sometimes they cook together and everyone makes his own dish.</br>
            <strong>James tends to prepare basic meals, usually the same 5/6 recipes. Sometimes he looks for recipes online</strong> and he makes his choice based on the picture and on the ingredients. </br>
            He used <strong>to alter recipes to follow his taste</strong> and his wife taste (she doesn’t like spicy food) but he doesn’t keep track of the alterations. The consequence is that <strong>he gets frustrated because recipes don’t taste the same every time.</strong>
            </p>
